detailResultFields.label: Course Section Definition Public Notes
detailResultFields.value:
Jewish, Christian, and Muslim Religious Traditions. Visit amne.ubc.ca for full course descriptions.

** This course has TWO required sections: a lecture and a discussion. This lecture section only meets MW. Please email amne.undergrad@ubc.ca with your ranked preference for Fridays discussion section. You will be assigned to a discussion section depending on your enrolment time and seat availability.**

The discussion sections are:
AMNE 160 L2A: F 12-1 pm
AMNE 160 L2B: F 1-2 pm
AMNE 160 L2C: F2-3 pm

If the course is full or blocked, or if you do not meet restrictions for the available seats, please register for the waitlist. Students will be moved manually from the waitlist into the course section. If the course is blocked by showing available seats, this is normal and means that waitlist transfer have not yet taken place. Email amne.undergrad@ubc.ca with any questions.

detailResultFields.value:
As students continue discovering Russian, they expand their vocabulary, learning new ways to enjoy pronouncing new sounds and meanings through engagement with contemporary and classical writers, songs, films, folklore, behaviours and etiquette customary in Russian-speaking contexts.

Interested in learning more about our courses within the Department of Central, Eastern and Northern European Studies? Click here.
